cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "OmniMed: A Multi-LLM Framework for Identifying Therapeutic microRNAs from Scientific Literature"
message: "If you use this software in your research, please cite it as below."
type: software
authors:
  - given-names: Chitrashen
    family-names: Sah
    affiliation: University of South Dakota
    orcid: "https://orcid.org/0009-0005-0842-817X"
abstract: >-
  OmniMed is an open-source, AI-powered research framework that queries multiple
  large language models in parallel to identify therapeutic microRNA (miRNA) and
  non-coding RNA candidates for cardiovascular disease from scientific literature.
  It synthesizes a consensus across models and scores each model against wet-lab
  experimental outcomes to build a reliability profile over time.
keywords:
  - microRNA
  - non-coding RNA
  - cardiovascular disease
  - large language models
  - biomedical research
  - multi-LLM
